  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Stroke is one of the major causes of death in the World. Many stroke survivors may suffer
      from long-term sequelae of stroke such as hemiplegia. The effects of rehabilitation therapy
      are limited. The development of new treatment strategies is essential. Repetitive
      transcranial magnetic stimulation (rTMS) is a non-invasive method to stimulate the focal area
      of the brain for restoring brain function. The aim of this study is to investigate the
      therapeutic effect of rTMS on the motor recovery in patients with hemiplegic stroke.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
