  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  stroke patients with motor weakness

          -  Medical research council (MRC) grade 0-4

          -  More than 2 weeks after stroke onset

          -  Age 18 years and older

          -  Able to provide consent for the protocol

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  History of previous symptomatic stroke

          -  pregnant women

          -  Persons with surgically or traumatically implanted foreign bodies such as a pacemaker,
             an implanted medication pump, a metal plate in the skull, or metal inside the skull or
             eyes (other than dental appliances or fillings), intracardiac lines that may pose a
             physical hazard during magnetic stimulation will also be excluded

          -  Patients with history of seizure disorder or epilepsy

          -  Subjects without the capacity to give informed consent
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
